MFM-300(Cr) was chosen as a photocatalyst because of its high stability and optical properties among the iso-structural family of MFM-300(MIII) (M = Al, Cr, V, Fe, Ga, In)36–39 materials. It is the only one that retains high crystallinity and stability after irradiation for 2 days under the photochemical conditions used in this work (Supplementary Fig. 6). Additionally, solid-state UV-Vis diffuse reflectance spectroscopy data confirm that MFM-300(Cr) has the widest window of light absorption up to 800 nm (Fig. 2a). The UV-Vis diffuse reflectance spectra of CrCl3·6H2O and H4L have also been measured (Supplementary Fig. 7). Three absorption bands centred at 289, 453 and 624 nm are observed for CrCl3·6H2O, which can be assigned to the d–d transitions of Cr3+, i.e., 4A2g→\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
